°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place drained chickpeas, pepper, salt, ¼ tsp curry powder and olive oil into a large bowl and toss to combine. Place chickpeas onto prepared baking tray and bake for 20 minutes (200°C) or until chickpeas are crispy."},{"content":"Carefully remove bay leaves from soup. Add cream and purée <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>, <b>increasing speed gradually to speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Divide soup between bowls, then season with pepper and garnish with crispy chickpeas just before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Meat or Vegetable stock paste recipes."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","50m","6 portions"]}